**requirements.txt** (Dependencies):
```
Flask==2.0.1
Flask-SQLAlchemy==2.5.1
```

To run the application:
1. Create the virtual environment and install dependencies:
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

2. Run the application:
```bash
python app.py
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:5000`. Features include:
- Adding new tasks
- Marking tasks as completed/not completed
- Filtering tasks (all/active/completed)
- Deleting tasks
- Responsive design

The database (SQLite) will be automatically created in the instance folder when you first run the application.